main event: On August 12, 1966, seven yellowish white objects were observed moving south in Minot, North Dakota.
interesting points: The observation lasted for about 3 seconds., The objects were described as disc-shaped and had a continuous yellowish white glow., A total of 8 objects were reported in formation., The observation was made by an Air Force member repairing a vehicle in a parking lot., Meteors were also noted in the area at the same time.
witness description: David E. Sutterfield, A3c, USAF, 86244 Transportation Squadron
